---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

export const prerender = true;
---

<Layout 
  title="Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy - Track Your Labs"
  description="How Track Your Labs protects your consumer health data under state privacy laws."
>
  <main class="flex-1 px-4 md:px-8 lg:px-10 pb-6 md:pb-8 lg:pb-10 pt-20 max-w-4xl mx-auto w-full">
    <div class="prose prose-gray max-w-full break-words">
      <h1 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold mb-4">Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy</h1>
      
      <p class="text-sm italic mb-6">Last updated: April 23, 2025</p>
      
      <p class="break-words">
        This Consumer Health Data Privacy Policy ("CHD Policy") explains how <strong>Snowflake Health, LLC</strong> ("Snowflake Health," "we," "our," or "us") collects, uses, discloses, and stores <strong>Consumer Health Data</strong> as defined under certain U.S. state laws, including the Washington My Health My Data Act ("MHMD"), Nevada Senate Bill 370, and similar emerging regulations. It supplements our <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">main Privacy Policy</a> and prevails where it provides stricter protections.
      </p>
      
      <div class="bg-gray-100 p-3 md:p-4 rounded-md my-6">
        <p class="font-bold">Plain‑language snapshot</p>
        <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
          <li>We only collect health data needed to deliver your lipid‑panel tests and AI coaching.</li>
          <li>We do <strong>not</strong> sell consumer health data.</li>
          <li>You can access, delete, or withdraw consent at any time.</li>
          <li>This policy applies to residents of Washington, Nevada, and any other state with similar laws.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">1. Scope & Definitions</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Consumer Health Data (CHD)</strong> – Personally identifiable data that is linked or reasonably linkable to you and reveals or relates to your past, present, or future physical or mental health condition, diagnosis, treatment, or bodily function, as defined by applicable state law.</li>
        <li><strong>Processing</strong> – Collection, use, storage, disclosure, or sharing of CHD.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        This Policy covers CHD processed via <strong>trackyourlabs.com</strong>, our mobile apps, phone support, email, and any related services.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">2. Types of Consumer Health Data We Collect</h2>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto -mx-4 md:mx-0">
        <div class="min-w-full inline-block align-middle">
          <table class="min-w-full border-collapse border border-gray-300 text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[120px]">Category</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[150px]">Examples</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[130px]">Primary Purpose</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Laboratory Data</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">LDL, HDL, Triglycerides, Total Cholesterol, test dates, lab location</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Provide lipid‑panel results and track trends</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">AI Coach Interactions</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Questions about diet, exercise, medications; AI recommendations</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Generate personalized guidance</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Self‑Reported Health Info</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Lifestyle habits, dietary preferences, family history</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Tailor advice and improve coaching accuracy</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Critical Result Flags</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Clinician‑noted critical values, follow‑up status</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Ensure timely safety notifications</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        We do <strong>not</strong> intentionally collect genetic data, reproductive health data, or mental‑health therapy notes.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">3. Sources of CHD</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>You</strong> – When you enter information or interact with the AI coach.</li>
        <li><strong>Laboratory Partners</strong> – Labcorp, Quest Diagnostics, or at‑home kit vendors send results to us.</li>
        <li><strong>Physician Network</strong> – Provides test authorization and may annotate critical results.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">4. How We Use Consumer Health Data</h2>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Deliver Services</strong> – Order tests, display results, generate AI insights, send reminders.</li>
        <li><strong>Improve Services</strong> – De‑identify and aggregate CHD to enhance our algorithms and features.</li>
        <li><strong>Safety & Compliance</strong> – Detect critical values, fulfill HIPAA record‑keeping, respond to lawful requests.</li>
        <li><strong>User Support</strong> – Troubleshoot issues, answer questions.</li>
      </ol>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        We will seek <strong>separate, opt‑in consent</strong> before using CHD for any materially different purpose.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">5. Disclosure of Consumer Health Data</h2>
      <p class="break-words">We only disclose CHD to:</p>
      <div class="overflow-x-auto -mx-4 md:mx-0 mt-4">
        <div class="min-w-full inline-block align-middle">
          <table class="min-w-full border-collapse border border-gray-300 text-sm">
            <thead>
              <tr class="bg-gray-100">
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[120px]">Recipient</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[150px]">Purpose</th>
                <th class="border border-gray-300 p-2 text-left min-w-[120px]">Legal Basis</th>
              </tr>
            </thead>
            <tbody>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Laboratory vendors</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Perform tests and upload results</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">HIPAA business‑associate agreements</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Physician network</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Review and approve orders; handle critical flags</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">HIPAA BAA</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Cloud hosting</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Secure data storage</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Data‑processing addendum; encryption</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Analytics (internal)</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Product improvement using de‑identified data</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Legitimate interest</td>
              </tr>
              <tr>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2 font-medium">Authorities</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Respond to subpoenas or legal orders</td>
                <td class="border border-gray-300 p-2">Legal obligation</td>
              </tr>
            </tbody>
          </table>
        </div>
      </div>
      
      <p class="mt-4 break-words">
        We <strong>do not sell or share</strong> CHD with advertising networks or other third parties for cross‑context behavioral advertising.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">6. Your Rights Over Consumer Health Data</h2>
      <p class="break-words">Depending on your state of residence, you may have the following rights:</p>
      <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li><strong>Access</strong> – Obtain a list of CHD categories and specific pieces we hold.</li>
        <li><strong>Deletion</strong> – Request deletion of CHD, subject to HIPAA or legal retention requirements.</li>
        <li><strong>Withdrawal of Consent</strong> – Revoke consent for processing non‑essential CHD.</li>
        <li><strong>Data Portability</strong> – Receive a copy in a structured, machine‑readable format.</li>
        <li><strong>Appeal</strong> – If we deny your request, you may appeal by emailing <em>legal@trackyourlabs.com</em>.</li>
      </ol>
      
      <h3 class="text-lg md:text-xl font-bold mt-6 mb-2">How to Exercise Your Rights</h3>
      <p class="break-words">
        Submit requests via <strong>Dashboard → Settings → Privacy</strong> or email <strong>privacy@trackyourlabs.com</strong>. We will verify identity (e.g., email confirmation + two data points) and respond within 45 days (90 days if reasonably necessary with notice).
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">7. Consent Management</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li>We obtain <strong>affirmative, written consent</strong> during signup to collect and process CHD.</li>
        <li>You may withdraw consent at any time in your dashboard; this may limit our ability to provide services.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">8. Retention & De‑Identification</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mt-2 break-words">
        <li>CHD linked to your account is retained while you are a subscriber and for <strong>7 years</strong> thereafter to comply with HIPAA.</li>
        <li>We store AI chat transcripts for <strong>up to 3 years</strong> unless you delete them sooner.</li>
        <li>Aggregated analytics datasets are <strong>de‑identified</strong> in compliance with HIPAA Safe Harbor or expert determination.</li>
      </ul>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">9. Security Measures</h2>
      <p class="break-words">
        Refer to Section 5 of our <a href="/privacy-policy" class="text-blue-600 hover:underline">main Privacy Policy</a> for encryption, access controls, audits, and incident‑response procedures. We follow HIPAA and NIST SP 800‑53‑aligned security frameworks to safeguard CHD.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">10. Changes to This CHD Policy</h2>
      <p class="break-words">
        We may update this Policy to reflect changes in law or our practices. We will post the revised Policy and notify you via email or in‑app message at least <strong>30 days</strong> before material changes take effect.
      </p>
      
      <hr class="my-8" />
      
      <h2 class="text-xl md:text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">11. Contact Us</h2>
      <blockquote class="bg-gray-100 p-3 md:p-4 rounded-md my-4 border-l-4 border-gray-400">
        <p><strong>Privacy Office – Consumer Health Data</strong></p>
        <p>Snowflake Health, LLC</p>
        <p class="break-all"><strong>Email:</strong> privacy@trackyourlabs.com</p>
      </blockquote>
      
      <p class="break-words">
        If you believe your CHD rights have been violated, you may also contact your state Attorney General.
      </p>
    </div>
  </main>
  
  <Footer />
</Layout>

<style>
  .prose {
    max-width: none;
  }
  
  .prose table {
    width: 100%;
  }
  
  .prose blockquote {
    font-style: normal;
  }
</style>